24
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:15,000
 And Eusebius of Caesarea, who was astonished by the emperor Constantin, was hopeful about humankind, humankind's potential to build the kingdom of God on earth.

25
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:24,000
 He believed a righteous emperor could rule over the Christian kingdom, returning the world to the paradisical experience of the Garden of Eden.

26
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:30,000
 In Eusebius' view, there could be no separation between politics and religion.

27
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:35,000
 Church patriarchs and the Roman emperors would rule together in divine harmony.

28
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:43,000
 These two visions would have profound implications for political and theological development going forward.

29
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:49,000
 In the east, Eusebius' harmonious vision would quickly devolve into Caesaropapism.

30
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:58,000
